  16 Jun 2008; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r4.ebuild:
  Marked ppc stable.

  21 Mar 2008; Samuli Suominen <drac@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r4.ebuild:
  amd64 stable

  05 Feb 2008; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r4.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64

  23 Jan 2008; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r4.ebuild:
  alpha/ia64/sparc/x86 stable

*corefonts-1-r4 (10 Jul 2007)

  10 Jul 2007; Ryan Hill <dirtyepic@gentoo.org> -corefonts-1-r3.ebuild,
  +corefonts-1-r4.ebuild:
  Remove Tahoma font as the missing bold face is negatively affecting the font
  quality of common web pages and apps. Thanks to Peter Ansell for bug
  #184790.

*corefonts-1-r3 (24 Jun 2007)

  24 Jun 2007; Ryan Hill <dirtyepic@gentoo.org> +corefonts-1-r3.ebuild:
  Install the Tahoma font, which was previously omitted due to licensing
  issues. Thanks to Christoph Brill in Bug #141219.

  18 Apr 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Add ~x86-fbsd keyword.

  23 Mar 2006; Donnie Berkholz <spyderous@gentoo.org>; -corefonts-1.ebuild,
  -corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  Get rid of ebuilds unported to modular X, breaking category-level commits.

  08 May 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  stable on ia64

  29 Dec 2004; Ciaran McCreesh <ciaranm@gentoo.org> :
  Change encoding to UTF-8 for GLEP 31 compliance

  16 Dec 2004; Dylan Carlson <absinthe@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64.

  14 Dec 2004; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64

  08 Nov 2004; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc-macos.

  04 Nov 2004; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc

  04 Nov 2004; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r2.ebuild,
  corefonts-1.ebuild:
  Removed cabextract from RDEPEND; bug #69601. Marked 1-r2 stable on x86,
  alpha and ppc.

  01 Nov 2004; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org>

  corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Marked ~ppc64; bug #68103

*corefonts-1-r2 (01 Oct 2004)

  01 Oct 2004; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> +corefonts-1-r2.ebuild:
  Adopted font.eclass; see bug #53965.

  29 Sep 2004; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  Make X optional; bug #53965.

  22 Aug 2004; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha.

  06 Aug 2004; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc

  27 Jul 2004; Donnie Berkholz <spyderous@gentoo.org>; corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  stable on x86, since xorg-x11 is stable and lots of people want these.

  15 Feb 2004; Donnie Berkholz <spyderous@gentoo.org>; metadata.xml:
  Adding metadata.xml.

  15 Feb 2004; Donnie Berkholz <spyderous@gentoo.org>; corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  Adding hints about /etc/fonts/local.conf.

*corefonts-1-r1 (03 Feb 2004)

  03 Feb 2004; <augustus@gentoo.org> corefonts-1-r1.ebuild:
  Fixed installion of corefonts to depend on x11 and to install the fonts.scale
  and fonts.dir files. Also added the hints about XF86Config changes. Added
  ~amd64 keyword.

  25 Jan 2004; Sven Blumenstein <bazik@gentoo.org> corefonts-1.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc.

  05 Dec 2003; <agriffis@gentoo.org> corefonts-1.ebuild:
  Stable on ia64

  22 Oct 2003; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> corefonts-1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha

*corefonts-1 (02 Jul 2003)

  02 Jul 2003; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Initial import.  Ebuild submitted by me for jpgraph support.
  Ripped code from the xfree ebuild.
